@Phil -- The clues as written don't describe their answers, but if you drop the "ab" from the clues, they do describe them.  Thus, [Viable investment plans] does not describe PONZI SCHEMES, but when you drop the "ab", the clue becomes [Vile investment plans], which is a legitimate clue for that answer.

The clue for the revealer RIPPED ABS says that the "ab"s must be ripped, or taken away, from the starred clues, to make them make sense.

I hope this makes sense!

